|Details = [[Amethyst]] is currently the highest level [[ore]] players can mine. It is used in the creation of high-level [[ranging]] [[ammo]]. At high [[Mining]] levels, players can expect to mine anywhere from 80 to 100 amethyst per hour for profits of {{NoCoins|{{GEP|Amethyst|80}}}}-{{NoCoins|{{GEP|Amethyst|100}}}} coins. Players may wish to bring a chisel with them to craft [[amethyst bolt tips]], [[amethyst arrowtips|arrowtips]], [[amethyst javelin heads|javelin heads]] or [[amethyst dart tip| dart tips]]. These stack in your inventory allowing you to avoid banking indefinitely, further decreasing the intensity. Due to the nature of the Grand Exchange, crafting Amethyst into other products can cut into the overall profit. Furthermore, crafting Amethyst is a longer process than simply banking the ore. Unidentified Minerals may be exchanged for mining gloves, superior mining gloves or soft clay packs, and bags full of gems at Belona's [[Mining Guild Mineral Exchange]].
